sections.body:
If your password includes special characters, and you are using your
password in a connection string URI, encode the special characters.

If you try to update a password with a special character that requires
[percent encoding](https://tools.ietf.org/html/3986#section-2.1), the following error message
appears:

```
This password contains special characters which will be URL-encoded.
```

> **Note:** The following characters and the space character must be converted
> using [percent encoding](https://tools.ietf.org/html/3986#section-2.1) if included in a
> username or password:
>
> ```none
> : / ? # [ ] @ ! $ & ' ( ) * , ; = %
> ```
>
> For example, if your password in plain-text is `p@ssw0rd'9'!`, you
> need to encode your password as:
>
> ```none
> p%40ssw0rd%279%27%21
> ```

***

